"tag-supplication-al-dua"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-9o9","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":5394,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/19\/dua-for-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":0},"title":"Abu Umamah on Eid: Companions ask Allah to accept good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: I was with Abu Umamah al-Bahili and others among the Companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. When they would return from Eid prayer, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Imam Ahmad said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25003,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/06\/12\/best-clothes-on-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Wear your best clothes on Eid","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 12, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would wear his best clothes on the days of the two Eids. Source: al-Sunan al-Kubra\u0301 lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 6143 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0641\u0650\u0639\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0633\u064f \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0633\u064e\u0646\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19587,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/ghusl-before-eid-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Perform Ghusl before attending Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, used to perform a ritual bath\u00a0on the day of Eid\u00a0before he would depart\u00a0for prayer. Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 609 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi Imam al-Nawawi commented, \"The narrations of Al-Shafi'i and his companions agree upon the recommendation to perform\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36091,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/hasan-taqabbal-allahu-minna\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":3},"title":"Hasan on Eid: May Allah accept from us and from you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Hawshab ibn \u2018Aqil reported: I met Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, on the day of Eid and I said, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Al-Hasan said, \u201cYes, may Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: al-Du\u2019a\u0304\u2019 li-T\u0323abara\u0304ni 930 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/taqabbal-allahu-minna-minkum\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":4},"title":"Umar II on Eid: May Allah accept from us and from you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Adham reported: We would say to Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, on the two Eids, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you, O commander of the faithful.\u201d He would return it to us and he did not reject that from us. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19598,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/eid-takbir-imam-arrives\/","url_meta":{"origin":36093,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Pronouncing Takbir until the Imam arrives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would depart to the Eid prayer from the mosque and he would raise his voice, declaring the greatness of Allah until he arrived at the place of prayer. He would continue to exalt Allah until the Imam arrived. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/36093","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=36093"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/36093\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=36093"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=36093"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=36093"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}